Troubleshooting
===============

<div class="warning">This documentation is currently out-of-date, and is in the process of being rewritten.  It should be completed within the next week or so.</div>

If you are experiencing problems with either the Student Robotics hardware, IDE or python library you should check here first to see if there is a simple solution. If you don't find the information you need in this section you can use the [forum](forum) to get help with your specific problem.

1. [Hardware issues](/docs/troubleshooting/hardware) &mdash; Common problems with the SR hardware and possible solutions.
2. [IDE issues](/docs/troubleshooting/ide) &mdash; Common problems with the SR IDE and possible solutions.
3. [`sr` python library issues](/docs/troubleshooting/python) &mdash; Common problems with the `sr` python library and possible solutions.
